In short:

The newsletter is technical, I'm not entirely.
My Twitter feed makes you reliant on me.
The newsletter gives you the tools to analyze the market yourself.

If you want to be a follower, Twitter is excellent.
If you want to learn how to trade/think, try the newsletter.

Both have their up and downsides.

While my system allows me to fish for tops and bottoms it also leads to me shorting/longing too early resulting in being stuck off-side.
A rigid technical system doesn't care about catching the bottom or top, it cares about the meat of the move.

A few people asked why TechnicalRoundup is still leaning bullish while I'm leaning bearish.

The newsletter follows a rigid technical system, it's bullish at support and careful at resistance.

I, on the other hand, follow a loose system.

@nanoissuperior The newsletter is PURELY technical and therefore bullish as long as support does its job.
If support fails it'll flip bearish.
I myself am not purely technical, I'll anticipate supports to fail before they've done so.

One follows a trend, the other follows its gut.

@nanoissuperior The newsletter is both Cred and mine.
When we disagree we maintain the stance that above support = bullish below support = bearish.
Very straight forward.
I think support will fail but technically the chart is still bullish.
